  <data name="BtnKillAlarm.ToolTip" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Grbl's alarm mode is a state when something has gone critically wrong, such as a hard limit or an abort during a cycle, or if Grbl doesn't know its position. 
By default, if you have homing enabled and power-up the Arduino, Grbl enters the alarm state, because it does not know its position. 
The alarm mode will lock all G-code commands until the '$H' homing cycle has been performed. </value>
    <comment>tt</comment>
